cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper focuses on building an architecture dataset on CIFAR-100 and conducting experiments on Tiny-ImageNet and ImageNet, which are all related to computer vision tasks. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes an efficient one-shot layer assignment search approach via inherited sampling, which is a machine learning technique. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper deals with neural architecture search, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper investigates the impact of different layer assignments on network performance, which is related to neural computing. 
5. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): Although the paper does not directly focus on hardware architecture, the proposed method can be applied to optimize the hardware architecture of neural networks, which makes it relevant to this sub-category.
